1
00:00:04,215 --> 00:00:06,315
(Love In Sync)

2
00:00:13,155 --> 00:00:15,625
(Kim Myung Soo)

3
00:00:19,765 --> 00:00:22,295
(Kang Min Ah)

4
00:00:42,015 --> 00:00:45,185
(Love In Sync)

5
00:00:47,025 --> 00:00:48,094
(All people, incidents, and backgrounds...)

6
00:00:48,095 --> 00:00:49,224
(in this drama are fictitious and unrelated to reality.)

7
00:00:49,225 --> 00:00:50,425
(Also, children and animals were filmed under production guidelines.)

8
00:00:52,795 --> 00:00:54,164
Ha Yul, we're out of time.

9
00:00:54,165 --> 00:00:58,905
Wash up quickly and wear the clothes Daddy laid out for you...

10
00:01:03,705 --> 00:01:05,075
Of course you wouldn't just put them on.

11
00:01:06,375 --> 00:01:08,615
Okay. Fine, good.

12
00:01:09,475 --> 00:01:10,745
Let's at least take off the crown.

13
00:01:11,015 --> 00:01:13,385
No. A princess has to wear a crown.

14
00:01:13,615 --> 00:01:16,685
Right now, you look more like a clown than a princess.

15
00:01:18,525 --> 00:01:19,885
Then at least take off the dress.

16
00:01:19,955 --> 00:01:21,725
Who goes to kindergarten dressed like this?

17
00:01:21,955 --> 00:01:25,695
- I do. - People will judge me.

18
00:01:25,925 --> 00:01:27,735
But I'm not the one they'll be judging.

19
00:01:33,775 --> 00:01:35,435
What's this? Is someone moving in across the hall?

20
00:01:35,875 --> 00:01:37,105
It's been empty for years.

21
00:01:38,975 --> 00:01:41,515
- Oh, I'm sorry. Are you okay? - Oh, I'm fine...

22
00:01:45,445 --> 00:01:47,755
- You're... - What are you doing here?

23
00:01:48,515 --> 00:01:50,885
Miss, where should I put this?

24
00:01:53,425 --> 00:01:55,455
Don't tell me you're moving in across the hall.

25
00:01:59,465 --> 00:02:01,635
Dad, what are you doing? We're late.

26
00:02:02,495 --> 00:02:03,535
Okay.

27
00:02:04,565 --> 00:02:05,605
Dad?

28
00:02:14,775 --> 00:02:17,515
Seriously? Of all the places in Seoul, why my neighbourhood?

29
00:02:18,045 --> 00:02:20,415
Why did it have to be right across the hall? This is so awkward.

30
00:02:27,755 --> 00:02:28,824
Dad, what are you doing?

31
00:02:28,825 --> 00:02:30,695
- We're late. - Dad?

32
00:02:31,465 --> 00:02:33,695
Who cares if she misunderstands?

33
00:02:33,935 --> 00:02:36,965
(Cha Eun Hwan)

34
00:02:40,035 --> 00:02:41,935
What? "Dad?"

35
00:02:43,575 --> 00:02:46,105
He's a married man, and he pretended to be single so perfectly...

36
00:02:49,845 --> 00:02:50,845
Well, he never actually said he was married.

37
00:02:52,245 --> 00:02:53,245
Right.

38
00:02:57,385 --> 00:03:00,895
- Ji An, are you okay? - I can't breathe.

39
00:03:01,455 --> 00:03:02,725
Look at me. Look into my eyes.

40
00:03:03,195 --> 00:03:05,525
Okay, now just do what I do. All right?

41
00:03:05,595 --> 00:03:08,164
What's your deal, mister? Are you Yu Ji An's lawyer or something?

42
00:03:08,165 --> 00:03:09,895
No, I'm a counsellor.

43
00:03:20,005 --> 00:03:22,045
Why won't this box open?

44
00:03:33,185 --> 00:03:35,295
Oh my, you're here?

45
00:03:36,095 --> 00:03:37,695
Isn't today your hospital appointment?

46
00:03:38,165 --> 00:03:39,665
I wasn't feeling well, so I postponed it.

47
00:03:39,725 --> 00:03:40,735
But what brings you here?

48
00:03:42,065 --> 00:03:44,135
I thought I'd do some cleaning while you were out...

49
00:03:44,765 --> 00:03:46,735
I thought I asked you to leave this room alone.

50
00:03:47,005 --> 00:03:49,675
But I'm paid to do this, how can I not?

51
00:03:49,905 --> 00:03:53,075
I'll just tidy up a bit, so you get back to work.

52
00:04:02,115 --> 00:04:04,655
I searched everywhere, her room and her studio,

53
00:04:04,855 --> 00:04:07,695
but it looks like she's serious this time. It's completely clean.

54
00:04:08,195 --> 00:04:11,265
Not a single soju bottle, not even a cider bottle that looks like one.

55
00:04:11,525 --> 00:04:13,495
Really? That's a relief.

56
00:04:13,765 --> 00:04:15,534
So you can relax, sir.

57
00:04:15,535 --> 00:04:17,535
After all the trouble she went through for treatment,

58
00:04:18,135 --> 00:04:21,305
there's no way her darn drinking problem will relapse, right?

59
00:04:21,705 --> 00:04:24,805
Even if she didn't raise her, she's still her mother.

60
00:04:25,105 --> 00:04:27,045
She'll get through this for the kid's sake.

61
00:04:27,545 --> 00:04:29,015
Yes, but just in case,

62
00:04:29,345 --> 00:04:31,415
please keep checking on her from time to time.

63
00:04:32,545 --> 00:04:33,545
Okay.

64
00:04:38,855 --> 00:04:39,855
Yes.

65
00:04:42,255 --> 00:04:45,865
- Sir, mail's from the Association. - From the Association?

66
00:04:45,925 --> 00:04:46,925
Yes.

67
00:04:47,535 --> 00:04:48,565
I wasn't expecting anything.

68
00:04:52,905 --> 00:04:56,005
(Summons To Disciplinary Committee, Attendee: Cha Eun Hwan)

69
00:04:58,375 --> 00:05:00,815
Don't tell me you've been referred to the Disciplinary Committee.

70
00:05:01,145 --> 00:05:03,985
No, no. What could you have possibly done wrong, sir?

71
00:05:13,225 --> 00:05:15,525
The boiler's broken on the very first day?

72
00:05:16,425 --> 00:05:19,095
Gosh, this is driving me crazy.

73
00:05:20,025 --> 00:05:22,065
It's cold.

74
00:05:31,505 --> 00:05:32,775
I wonder if she finished moving in okay.

75
00:05:35,275 --> 00:05:36,515
It's none of my business.

76
00:05:46,055 --> 00:05:48,825
- Are you okay? Are you hurt? - It's cold.

77
00:05:50,355 --> 00:05:51,795
It's so cold.

78
00:05:53,025 --> 00:05:54,035
Huh?

79
00:05:59,165 --> 00:06:00,905
First, let's go to my place.

80
00:06:09,575 --> 00:06:11,715
It's warm tea. Have some.

81
00:06:19,585 --> 00:06:22,495
So, while you were moving, the gas and the electricity...

82
00:06:22,755 --> 00:06:24,065
You didn't transfer all of them?

83
00:06:26,065 --> 00:06:27,565
It's not that I didn't know.

84
00:06:29,035 --> 00:06:30,295
I was so busy that I forgot.

85
00:06:33,305 --> 00:06:34,975
I thought she wasn't working these days.

86
00:06:38,705 --> 00:06:41,645
Publicly, that might be true, but personally, not at all.

87
00:06:42,115 --> 00:06:43,375
I've been incredibly busy.

88
00:06:44,385 --> 00:06:46,515
Getting fired from shows, getting scammed,

89
00:06:47,045 --> 00:06:48,055
and being humiliated.

90
00:06:50,415 --> 00:06:52,825
Can you hear my thoughts, by any chance?

91
00:06:54,255 --> 00:06:55,324
What?

92
00:06:55,325 --> 00:06:57,995
No, I'm sure I only thought that and didn't say it out loud.

93
00:06:58,365 --> 00:06:59,625
But you keep reading my mind.

94
00:07:02,765 --> 00:07:05,305
Well, actually, I also...

95
00:07:08,335 --> 00:07:10,535
Dad, I'm hungry.

96
00:07:11,175 --> 00:07:12,275
Ha Yul, you're awake?

97
00:07:17,615 --> 00:07:18,615
What are you staring at?

98
00:07:19,545 --> 00:07:21,855
What? Never seen a pretty girl before?

99
00:07:22,655 --> 00:07:23,655
Lady.

100
00:07:27,295 --> 00:07:28,295
Auntie.

101
00:07:29,655 --> 00:07:32,195
And now, the delicious curry is served.

102
00:07:37,465 --> 00:07:39,005
Are you sure you'll be okay not eating?

103
00:07:40,335 --> 00:07:43,275
I haven't eaten carbs after 6pm since I was 12.

104
00:07:43,875 --> 00:07:46,005
I'm more used to skipping meals than eating,

105
00:07:46,445 --> 00:07:47,845
so don't mind me and eat.

106
00:07:49,075 --> 00:07:51,215
But you should have something in your stomach when it's cold.

107
00:07:53,815 --> 00:07:56,415
- Well, should we dig in then? - Yes, Dad.

108
00:08:03,855 --> 00:08:04,865
Is it that bad?

109
00:08:11,665 --> 00:08:15,605
I wanted yummy curry. Yummy curry.

110
00:08:16,335 --> 00:08:17,545
You know, the thing about taste is,

111
00:08:18,745 --> 00:08:20,305
it can just be that you're not used to it.

112
00:08:21,245 --> 00:08:22,915
If you keep getting to know a flavour,

113
00:08:23,175 --> 00:08:25,015
something you don't like can become delicious.

114
00:08:30,185 --> 00:08:31,755
How about...

115
00:08:34,595 --> 00:08:37,425
No, what if your auntie works some magic on the curry?

116
00:09:22,375 --> 00:09:25,345
How are you such a good cook when you barely eat?

117
00:09:26,645 --> 00:09:29,045
Because no one ever cooked for me.

118
00:09:30,415 --> 00:09:33,115
So I wanted to at least cook for myself.

119
00:09:36,455 --> 00:09:37,725
Even though I can't eat it.

120
00:09:46,565 --> 00:09:48,795
I thought you'd be late. You finished up early.

121
00:09:49,495 --> 00:09:52,365
She moved in across the hall today, but her boiler is broken.

122
00:09:53,435 --> 00:09:55,475
So I told her to warm up here until the repairman comes.

123
00:09:56,575 --> 00:09:57,575
Hello.

124
00:09:59,305 --> 00:10:00,305
Hi.

125
00:10:06,615 --> 00:10:07,615
Cha Eun Hwan.

126
00:10:09,455 --> 00:10:10,455
What is going on?

127
00:10:23,765 --> 00:10:26,305
Ji An, I'm sorry,

128
00:10:27,905 --> 00:10:29,135
but could you please leave now?

129
00:10:30,205 --> 00:10:33,545
- What? Not done with my drink... - Just...

130
00:10:35,315 --> 00:10:36,515
I'm just asking you to leave.

131
00:10:41,085 --> 00:10:44,085
Fine. I'll leave. Happy now?

132
00:11:00,665 --> 00:11:02,605
What's with him? He's the one who invited me in.

133
00:11:03,005 --> 00:11:04,075
How annoying.

134
00:11:12,915 --> 00:11:13,945
Yu Ji An?

135
00:11:14,615 --> 00:11:15,915
What is she doing in our house?

136
00:11:16,315 --> 00:11:17,315
I already told you.

137
00:11:17,785 --> 00:11:19,325
She moved in across the hall by coincidence.

138
00:11:19,585 --> 00:11:21,855
Coincidence? More like a curse.

139
00:11:22,655 --> 00:11:24,665
- Tell her to move out tomorrow. - Song Hwan.

140
00:11:24,725 --> 00:11:27,995
On second thought. Let's move. It'll be faster.

141
00:11:29,965 --> 00:11:30,965
Don't tell me...

142
00:11:32,435 --> 00:11:34,405
You don't expect me to live here and see her every day, do you?

143
00:11:35,275 --> 00:11:38,175
I can barely breathe just seeing her on TV for a second.

144
00:11:38,945 --> 00:11:41,115
I get so furious that I'm going to lose my mind.

145
00:11:41,745 --> 00:11:44,745
- Do you still resent her that much? - And you don't?

146
00:11:45,515 --> 00:11:48,655
It was just an accident. The kind that's nobody's fault.

147
00:11:48,715 --> 00:11:49,815
I know, I know.

148
00:11:50,715 --> 00:11:52,985
But that accident made us lose everything.

149
00:11:54,755 --> 00:11:57,665
If it hadn't been for her, if that accident hadn't happened,

150
00:11:59,095 --> 00:12:01,465
I wouldn't have been living like this.

151
00:12:06,065 --> 00:12:07,365
My misery...

152
00:12:08,605 --> 00:12:09,805
It feels like it's all her fault,

153
00:12:09,875 --> 00:12:11,345
and the injustice is driving me insane.

154
00:12:14,275 --> 00:12:15,675
It was my fault too.

155
00:12:18,845 --> 00:12:20,545
You must be tired. Get some rest.

156
00:12:21,455 --> 00:12:22,615
About the real estate office,

157
00:12:24,555 --> 00:12:26,185
I'll stop by when I have time.

158
00:12:41,435 --> 00:12:43,505
(Exclusive Management Contract)

159
00:12:44,975 --> 00:12:47,645
Those are the best terms our company can offer.

160
00:12:48,145 --> 00:12:50,845
They don't exactly seem like the best.

161
00:12:52,085 --> 00:12:53,845
I hear things, you know.

162
00:12:55,585 --> 00:12:59,625
Why is it that the "best" for me and the "best" for Yu Ji An...

163
00:13:00,995 --> 00:13:02,194
are in completely different leagues?

164
00:13:02,195 --> 00:13:03,555
That's pretty upsetting.

165
00:13:07,095 --> 00:13:08,095
Yi Jin.

166
00:13:09,935 --> 00:13:13,665
Does any fool risk their life to win a neighbourhood soccer game?

167
00:13:14,475 --> 00:13:16,705
You save that for the international tournaments.

168
00:13:17,505 --> 00:13:18,505
Right?

169
00:13:20,805 --> 00:13:22,815
So you're saying I'm not in that league yet?

170
00:13:31,925 --> 00:13:35,725
Fine. I'll sign the contract, Mr. Kim. But...

171
00:13:36,455 --> 00:13:38,325
I have one more condition.

172
00:13:40,125 --> 00:13:42,835
There isn't a single person in this industry...

173
00:13:43,435 --> 00:13:45,205
who would sign you unless they are completely insane.

174
00:13:45,735 --> 00:13:48,275
Who's going to want an actress whose reputation is in shambles?

175
00:13:50,305 --> 00:13:52,405
If no one else will love me,

176
00:13:53,275 --> 00:13:55,345
then I'll just have to love myself.

177
00:13:57,745 --> 00:13:59,845
What? A one-person agency?

178
00:14:00,815 --> 00:14:01,815
Yes.

179
00:14:02,615 --> 00:14:05,355
I've been stuck in one place for years anyway.

180
00:14:05,755 --> 00:14:08,595
So, both as Yu Ji An the person and as Yu Ji An the actress,

181
00:14:09,595 --> 00:14:12,125
I've been feeling a little stagnant.

182
00:14:12,795 --> 00:14:14,534
Now that things have turned out this way,

183
00:14:14,535 --> 00:14:17,195
I want to use my own strength and my unique style...

184
00:14:17,435 --> 00:14:20,765
- to restart my acting career. - I see.

185
00:14:21,375 --> 00:14:23,935
The honour of joining me for that brilliant new beginning...

186
00:14:24,645 --> 00:14:25,845
I'm giving it to you.

187
00:14:30,245 --> 00:14:31,245
- What? - What?

188
00:14:32,585 --> 00:14:35,285
What? Are you just so overjoyed that you're speechless?

189
00:14:35,385 --> 00:14:36,385
No, it's just...

190
00:14:38,425 --> 00:14:40,485
Hey, you say it first.

191
00:14:41,395 --> 00:14:43,855
You started it, so you go first.

192
00:14:43,995 --> 00:14:46,195
- You go first. - Ever heard of ladies first?

193
00:14:51,205 --> 00:14:53,205
In these uncertain times,

194
00:14:53,305 --> 00:14:56,105
it's a bit much to ask us to switch companies just on your word.

195
00:14:56,605 --> 00:14:58,845
For stylists like us, our resumes are built...

196
00:14:58,905 --> 00:15:00,575
on the celebrities we work with.

197
00:15:01,115 --> 00:15:04,015
You know I'm the breadwinner in my family, right?

198
00:15:04,645 --> 00:15:09,255
I'm the sole provider for my mom back home and sibling's tuition...

199
00:15:09,855 --> 00:15:10,915
I'm sorry.

200
00:15:58,035 --> 00:16:00,435
- Sir, you can't do that. - What do you mean, I can't?

201
00:16:01,435 --> 00:16:03,235
Buy 1, get 1 free, right?

202
00:16:03,505 --> 00:16:06,605
- Why can't you give me the other? - The sale ended yesterday.

203
00:16:06,675 --> 00:16:08,145
Then you should've taken the sign down.

204
00:16:08,645 --> 00:16:10,615
Anyway, it's your mistake, so I'm taking this.

205
00:16:10,675 --> 00:16:12,815
- Sir, you can't. - What do you mean, I can't?

206
00:16:12,945 --> 00:16:13,945
Excuse me.

207
00:16:14,515 --> 00:16:16,755
- Look over here. - What?

208
00:16:16,815 --> 00:16:20,685
- Sir, you know who I am, right? - How would I know who you are?

209
00:16:22,325 --> 00:16:24,025
They say fame is fleeting.

210
00:16:25,965 --> 00:16:28,965
You're Yu Ji An, right? Oh, my gosh.

211
00:16:29,335 --> 00:16:32,535
- Yes. It's me. - Oh, the bullying one?

212
00:16:32,935 --> 00:16:37,535
Of course I do. The Nation's Brat. In this day and age,

213
00:16:37,605 --> 00:16:39,775
how dare you go on bullying? Jeez.

214
00:16:39,845 --> 00:16:42,674
You know that well, but why are you acting this way?

215
00:16:42,675 --> 00:16:44,484
- What? - Well...

216
00:16:44,485 --> 00:16:46,685
You want me to pass the "bullying" title on to you?

217
00:16:47,985 --> 00:16:51,085
My popularity may have dropped, but I still have all my followers.

218
00:16:51,155 --> 00:16:52,255
The second I post this video,

219
00:16:52,325 --> 00:16:54,595
I can make you the next bullying star of the nation.

220
00:16:57,825 --> 00:16:58,895
Darn it.

221
00:17:00,025 --> 00:17:01,025
Just one.

222
00:17:02,265 --> 00:17:03,465
Gosh.

223
00:17:12,475 --> 00:17:13,705
Thank you so much.

224
00:17:16,175 --> 00:17:18,215
Don't get me wrong. It's not fair for one person...

225
00:17:18,285 --> 00:17:20,745
to get 2 for the same price while another only gets 1.

226
00:17:21,515 --> 00:17:24,455
I can tolerate injustice, but I can't tolerate being shortchanged.

227
00:17:40,765 --> 00:17:44,475
Of course I know that bullying woman.

228
00:17:45,105 --> 00:17:46,345
The Nation's Brat.

229
00:18:26,585 --> 00:18:29,115
- Are you okay? - Yes.

230
00:18:29,815 --> 00:18:30,955
Well, that's a relief.

231
00:18:33,355 --> 00:18:34,355
All right then.

232
00:18:35,655 --> 00:18:36,725
Excuse me.

233
00:18:38,025 --> 00:18:39,025
Yes?

234
00:18:40,595 --> 00:18:42,565
Aren't you hungry?

235
00:18:44,495 --> 00:18:47,165
No, I'm not.

236
00:18:49,835 --> 00:18:51,205
Well, I am.

237
00:19:11,465 --> 00:19:12,665
But you said you were hungry?

238
00:19:14,465 --> 00:19:17,135
If I ate every time I was hungry, I couldn't maintain this figure.

239
00:19:17,295 --> 00:19:18,305
So?

240
00:19:19,635 --> 00:19:21,775
You want me to eat all of this by myself?

241
00:19:23,175 --> 00:19:24,535
Can't you just eat it?

242
00:19:27,275 --> 00:19:30,945
When I see someone in front of me enjoying their food,

243
00:19:31,075 --> 00:19:32,615
it makes me feel good.

244
00:19:34,045 --> 00:19:35,455
I guess it's a kind of vicarious satisfaction.

245
00:19:38,755 --> 00:19:42,855
To be honest, I'm feeling a bit down and bitter today.

246
00:19:46,765 --> 00:19:48,965
And since I happen to be a therapist,

247
00:19:49,035 --> 00:19:51,235
I can't stand to see someone so down.

248
00:19:55,405 --> 00:19:58,745
Okay. Which one? This one?

249
00:20:06,085 --> 00:20:08,085
Feeling any better?

250
00:20:09,155 --> 00:20:10,255
A little.

251
00:20:11,215 --> 00:20:12,955
Come on, you should have some too.

252
00:20:13,455 --> 00:20:15,895
Direct satisfaction is much better than vicarious satisfaction.

253
00:20:16,495 --> 00:20:17,495
Don't you think?

254
00:20:21,635 --> 00:20:23,095
If I cross that line,

255
00:20:24,295 --> 00:20:25,835
I'm afraid I really won't be able to go back.

256
00:20:36,175 --> 00:20:38,515
This is as far as I'll stray today.

257
00:20:45,755 --> 00:20:47,555
You don't need to pity me.

258
00:20:50,495 --> 00:20:51,495
Who does?

259
00:20:52,225 --> 00:20:53,395
Me? When?

260
00:20:54,095 --> 00:20:55,735
Oh, come on. You do.

261
00:20:58,235 --> 00:21:00,105
It's like you can feel exactly what I'm feeling...

262
00:21:03,605 --> 00:21:04,605
I know.

263
00:21:06,175 --> 00:21:07,945
It really feels like I can.

264
00:21:08,715 --> 00:21:09,715
What?

265
00:21:10,345 --> 00:21:11,845
That's ridiculous.

266
00:21:14,955 --> 00:21:16,885
It's almost like I can really hear it.

267
00:21:19,125 --> 00:21:20,125
What?

268
00:21:24,395 --> 00:21:26,365
I have to go. Something urgent came up.

269
00:21:26,465 --> 00:21:27,494
To celebrate the reunion with Ji An,

270
00:21:27,495 --> 00:21:29,665
the beef tartare is on the house. Go on in.

271
00:21:32,335 --> 00:21:34,265
Hey, what's with her?

272
00:21:34,605 --> 00:21:37,905
Hey. What the hell did you do to make our Ji An bolt like that?

273
00:21:38,005 --> 00:21:39,005
I don't know.

274
00:21:40,545 --> 00:21:43,875
Hey, but do you think she can read minds?

275
00:21:44,985 --> 00:21:45,985
Read minds?

276
00:21:47,115 --> 00:21:49,155
It's weird. She keeps guessing what I'm thinking.

277
00:21:52,085 --> 00:21:53,455
So,

278
00:21:53,625 --> 00:21:57,725
you're saying you keep hearing other people's voices?

279
00:21:58,565 --> 00:21:59,865
Strictly speaking,

280
00:22:00,365 --> 00:22:02,535
it's not multiple unspecified people.

281
00:22:03,165 --> 00:22:04,165
It's a specific person.

282
00:22:05,535 --> 00:22:07,405
Whenever I'm with this one man,

283
00:22:08,035 --> 00:22:10,935
it sometimes feels like I can hear his words directly,

284
00:22:11,235 --> 00:22:13,005
and other times, it's like...

285
00:22:13,245 --> 00:22:17,715
his feelings are being conveyed to me vaguely.

286
00:22:21,885 --> 00:22:22,955
Sounds strange, doesn't it?

287
00:22:26,085 --> 00:22:29,155
You've been under a lot of stress lately, haven't you?

288
00:22:29,555 --> 00:22:32,525
When you're suffering from extreme stress,

289
00:22:32,765 --> 00:22:34,835
you can sometimes experience auditory hallucinations.

290
00:22:35,095 --> 00:22:37,865
Okay, calming your mind and body is most important.

291
00:22:37,935 --> 00:22:41,305
- I'll prescribe you medication. - Could it be...

292
00:22:42,735 --> 00:22:44,505
that you can hear them because you like him?

293
00:22:45,445 --> 00:22:46,745
It's not something like that, is it?

294
00:22:47,705 --> 00:22:50,575
- Excuse me? - It's absolutely not like that.

295
00:22:51,075 --> 00:22:53,445
I may be a brat, but I still have a sense of ethics.

296
00:22:54,585 --> 00:22:55,685
I would never look at...

297
00:22:56,255 --> 00:22:58,285
another woman's man.

298
00:23:01,755 --> 00:23:02,795
Okay.

299
00:23:08,865 --> 00:23:11,805
Yes, I wouldn't believe me either.

300
00:23:13,235 --> 00:23:15,875
Feeling someone else's emotions? Gosh, that's insane.

301
00:23:22,115 --> 00:23:23,975
(Han Ji Hoon, CEO, Lumibella Cosmetics)

302
00:23:29,015 --> 00:23:32,855
(Complaint P: Han Ji-Hoon, CEO, D: Yu Ji An, Claim For Indemnity)

303
00:23:37,755 --> 00:23:38,925
I said let go.

304
00:23:43,865 --> 00:23:45,505
(CEO Kim Jun Sik)

305
00:23:45,705 --> 00:23:46,705
What is this?

306
00:23:46,965 --> 00:23:48,275
What do you mean a claim for indemnification?

307
00:23:48,605 --> 00:23:50,235
Don't tell me you're asking because you don't know what it means.

308
00:23:50,475 --> 00:23:53,775
Are you kidding me? You told me when we signed the contract,

309
00:23:53,845 --> 00:23:56,844
- the company would be responsible. - That's what I said.

310
00:23:56,845 --> 00:23:59,085
Then why the hell did I get served these papers?

311
00:24:02,315 --> 00:24:03,485
Look, Ji An.

312
00:24:04,055 --> 00:24:05,555
Like I always told you,

313
00:24:06,185 --> 00:24:08,825
you have to read contracts carefully.

314
00:24:09,525 --> 00:24:11,525
Regarding all penalty fees and legal disputes caused...

315
00:24:11,595 --> 00:24:13,625
by the artist during the contract period,

316
00:24:14,225 --> 00:24:15,995
the company will be fully responsible for them.

317
00:24:16,065 --> 00:24:19,065
Meaning, until when? During the contract period.

318
00:24:24,005 --> 00:24:27,445
Our contract ended on December 13, 2025,

319
00:24:27,545 --> 00:24:30,475
and the abuse of power controversy broke on December 24.

320
00:24:31,045 --> 00:24:32,685
So, about all the penalty fees and legal costs...

321
00:24:32,745 --> 00:24:34,015
that have come up since then,

322
00:24:34,185 --> 00:24:36,115
the company has no responsibility for them, right?

323
00:24:37,655 --> 00:24:40,985
That's why you should have just done it when I was trying...

324
00:24:41,055 --> 00:24:42,125
to persuade you to sign the renewal.

325
00:24:42,955 --> 00:24:44,965
Then you wouldn't have been left holding the bag like this.

326
00:24:46,065 --> 00:24:47,625
But you had to be stubborn, saying there was no rush.

327
00:24:50,035 --> 00:24:53,535
This amount is quite large. Can you handle it on your own?

328
00:24:54,865 --> 00:24:55,975
If it's too much,

329
00:24:56,435 --> 00:24:58,975
maybe you should try calling your mother in the States.

330
00:24:59,405 --> 00:25:01,605
After all, you're the one who earned all that money for her.

331
00:25:03,445 --> 00:25:06,115
You can spare me the fake sympathy.

332
00:25:06,415 --> 00:25:08,585
If you refuse, there's nothing I can do.

333
00:25:09,715 --> 00:25:11,385
If we're done here, would you please leave?

334
00:25:11,755 --> 00:25:13,755
I have a prior engagement. All right?

335
00:25:18,965 --> 00:25:20,125
Why are you here?

336
00:25:23,495 --> 00:25:25,105
And why are they standing next to her?

337
00:25:25,705 --> 00:25:27,065
Say hello.

338
00:25:29,235 --> 00:25:31,475
She's our company's new top star.

339
00:25:33,375 --> 00:25:37,275
And next to her is our company's elite team to support our new face.

340
00:25:45,085 --> 00:25:46,125
Ji An.

341
00:25:53,795 --> 00:25:54,825
Thanks.

342
00:25:57,195 --> 00:25:58,365
You know, I've been getting stabbed...

343
00:25:58,435 --> 00:25:59,805
in the back so much these past few days.

344
00:26:00,105 --> 00:26:01,705
I was losing my mind.

345
00:26:03,075 --> 00:26:05,605
But getting betrayed one last time like this...

346
00:26:06,775 --> 00:26:09,575
has snapped me back to my senses.

347
00:26:11,045 --> 00:26:12,885
You think I'm finished, don't you?

348
00:26:15,285 --> 00:26:16,485
As if.

349
00:26:17,355 --> 00:26:18,785
I'm Yu Ji An.

350
00:26:21,155 --> 00:26:23,025
Take a good look at me now.

351
00:26:23,855 --> 00:26:26,695
Because this is the last time you'll ever see me looking this pathetic.

352
00:26:29,335 --> 00:26:30,465
I'll be seeing you.

353
00:26:57,255 --> 00:26:58,565
(Ward A)

354
00:26:58,665 --> 00:27:00,395
That bastard isn't even 40,

355
00:27:00,565 --> 00:27:03,035
and he has 13 priors for fraud. That rotten bastard.

356
00:27:03,295 --> 00:27:04,795
A guy like that should be in prison,

357
00:27:04,865 --> 00:27:06,665
but an innocent person is locked up instead.

358
00:27:08,135 --> 00:27:10,234
He's in room 1501 at Anjun Hospital.

359
00:27:10,235 --> 00:27:12,105
It's a disgusting task, but what can you do?

360
00:27:12,505 --> 00:27:13,905
You'll just have to persuade him in a sweet manner.

361
00:27:15,475 --> 00:27:16,645
You psycho.

362
00:27:20,385 --> 00:27:21,385
Who the hell are you?

363
00:27:25,685 --> 00:27:26,785
So you're the one...

364
00:27:27,255 --> 00:27:30,025
who made me get stabbed through crappy counselling.

365
00:27:31,755 --> 00:27:33,795
You're that son of a gun counsellor.

366
00:27:35,135 --> 00:27:36,195
Hey, you bastard.

367
00:27:36,565 --> 00:27:39,105
If you're going to give advice, you should at least do it right.

368
00:27:39,265 --> 00:27:40,835
You had to go gaslighting some fool,

369
00:27:40,905 --> 00:27:42,335
talking about revenge and whatnot,

370
00:27:42,405 --> 00:27:44,875
and an innocent guy like me got stabbed because of it. Look.

371
00:27:45,275 --> 00:27:49,045
- Any idea how much this hurts? - Oh my, it must have hurt a lot.

372
00:27:49,345 --> 00:27:51,314
I mean, have you ever been stabbed?

373
00:27:51,315 --> 00:27:53,885
Man, this thing hurts so... Gosh. What the hell?

374
00:27:54,285 --> 00:27:57,015
Hey, you psycho. Hey. My stomach. Mom.

375
00:27:57,285 --> 00:27:58,655
What a shame.

376
00:27:59,325 --> 00:28:03,125
- What? - You almost took a fall.

377
00:28:03,255 --> 00:28:05,725
Jeez, seriously. Hey, what's your deal?

378
00:28:05,895 --> 00:28:07,725
Who the hell are you to come here and start trouble?

379
00:28:09,795 --> 00:28:11,665
I hear you refused to settle with Lee Young Ji.

380
00:28:11,795 --> 00:28:12,835
Of course I did.

381
00:28:12,965 --> 00:28:15,875
You think I'm crazy enough to settle with the gun who stabbed me?

382
00:28:16,275 --> 00:28:18,035
It's not like I'd get anything from her.

383
00:28:19,875 --> 00:28:20,875
I see.

384
00:28:22,045 --> 00:28:25,145
You're here to ask me to settle.

385
00:28:25,485 --> 00:28:28,555
But you're the one in a bind. So why the cocky attitude?

386
00:28:28,815 --> 00:28:30,115
It is about a settlement,

387
00:28:31,385 --> 00:28:32,555
but I'm not here to ask.

388
00:28:33,725 --> 00:28:34,725
It's a threat.

389
00:28:35,425 --> 00:28:37,125
What? A threat?

390
00:28:41,765 --> 00:28:45,635
You started with scams involving used goods at 18, and now you're 39.

391
00:28:46,165 --> 00:28:47,465
You've done scams involving crypto,

392
00:28:47,535 --> 00:28:49,035
gift cards, employment, and real estate.

393
00:28:50,075 --> 00:28:51,805
You have quite the colourful resume.

394
00:28:52,875 --> 00:28:56,145
Well, I get bored easily.

395
00:28:57,445 --> 00:29:00,615
You have 13 priors. If we count the times you got away with it,

396
00:29:00,885 --> 00:29:03,255
the number of victims...

397
00:29:04,185 --> 00:29:07,625
is enough to fill an entire school field, right?

398
00:29:09,055 --> 00:29:11,925
So, what's your point?

399
00:29:13,525 --> 00:29:16,635
From now on, I'm going to track down every single one of your victims,

400
00:29:16,765 --> 00:29:21,365
and I'm going to counsel them. Just like I did with Lee Young Ji.

401
00:29:24,635 --> 00:29:27,675
Get angry. Don't hold back.

402
00:29:30,215 --> 00:29:31,245
Make him pay.

403
00:29:33,085 --> 00:29:36,385
If I keep that up, maybe a few of those "fools," as you called them,

404
00:29:36,955 --> 00:29:38,955
will end up being gaslighted by me too, don't you think?

405
00:29:44,755 --> 00:29:46,325
You got lucky this time,

406
00:29:47,995 --> 00:29:50,535
but there's no guarantee you'll be lucky every time, is there?

407
00:29:51,395 --> 00:29:53,635
You... You bastard.

408
00:29:54,365 --> 00:29:57,005
So if you don't want to get stabbed to death,

409
00:29:59,145 --> 00:30:00,475
you'd better think carefully.

410
00:30:05,385 --> 00:30:06,815
Hey, you son of a gun. Are you crazy?

411
00:30:08,385 --> 00:30:09,755
I heard you're facing the Disciplinary Committee.

412
00:30:10,555 --> 00:30:12,255
And that they're holding a hearing?

413
00:30:12,755 --> 00:30:15,185
If word gets out about what you did today, you're...

414
00:30:18,665 --> 00:30:19,695
Are you insane?

415
00:30:20,625 --> 00:30:22,494
You said you're not legally responsible,

416
00:30:22,495 --> 00:30:24,265
so why are you going nuts over this?

417
00:30:27,935 --> 00:30:30,075
I may not be legally responsible,

418
00:30:30,675 --> 00:30:33,045
but my conscience is killing me.

419
00:30:34,505 --> 00:30:36,345
A so-called counsellor...

420
00:30:37,115 --> 00:30:39,085
Because a counsellor did such a shitty job,

421
00:30:39,185 --> 00:30:41,515
an innocent person is going to jail.

422
00:30:42,755 --> 00:30:44,355
If my conscience didn't bother me, would I even be human?

423
00:30:46,885 --> 00:30:50,225
A bastard who uses people's emotions for his own success.

424
00:30:52,495 --> 00:30:54,025
How can I call myself a counsellor?

425
00:30:57,365 --> 00:30:58,465
Still, man.

426
00:30:59,135 --> 00:31:00,235
After all,

427
00:31:01,335 --> 00:31:04,175
there's no counsellor more sincere with their clients than you.

428
00:31:05,545 --> 00:31:07,205
You empathize more than anyone,

429
00:31:07,845 --> 00:31:09,315
and comfort them more than anyone.

430
00:31:11,075 --> 00:31:13,545
I can vouch for that. I know what I'm talking about.

431
00:31:14,015 --> 00:31:15,215
Don't be discouraged.

432
00:31:16,355 --> 00:31:17,415
You're doing great.

433
00:31:25,255 --> 00:31:26,295
I'm leaving.

434
00:31:29,635 --> 00:31:32,535
That poor bastard.

435
00:31:45,045 --> 00:31:47,915
Right. Pride won't pay the bills.

436
00:31:58,895 --> 00:32:03,595
CEO, I hope you're doing well. It's Ji An.

437
00:32:05,735 --> 00:32:08,165
What do you mean, "which one?" Yu Ji An, of course.

438
00:32:08,535 --> 00:32:12,035
You once said you wanted to sign a contract with me.

439
00:32:12,605 --> 00:32:14,345
You even said you'd pay my penalty.

440
00:32:14,405 --> 00:32:17,015
Sorry. I'm just so busy right now...

441
00:32:17,775 --> 00:32:19,445
Busy?

442
00:32:19,815 --> 00:32:21,785
Right, right. Okay, then I'll call you some other time...

443
00:32:31,995 --> 00:32:35,865
Director, hi. It's Ji An.

444
00:32:36,195 --> 00:32:37,265
Who is this?

445
00:32:37,895 --> 00:32:39,635
Excuse me, who are you?

446
00:32:41,605 --> 00:32:43,405
What? Did he change his number?

447
00:32:45,035 --> 00:32:46,045
The number you dialled is unavailable.

448
00:32:49,775 --> 00:32:52,945
Director, this is Ji An.

449
00:32:53,145 --> 00:32:55,385
Please call me back when you get a chance.

450
00:33:01,125 --> 00:33:04,725
- Hello? - Gosh. Writer Oh.

451
00:33:07,095 --> 00:33:08,665
Thank you, Writer Oh.

452
00:33:09,335 --> 00:33:11,534
Of the 100 people in my contacts,

453
00:33:11,535 --> 00:33:14,805
you're the only one who agreed to see me.

454
00:33:16,535 --> 00:33:18,174
You know this industry is all about...

455
00:33:18,175 --> 00:33:20,275
using people and tossing them aside, right?

456
00:33:24,145 --> 00:33:26,645
Still, I never thought it'd be this bad.

457
00:33:27,115 --> 00:33:30,115
I know. You should've been nicer when you were on top.

458
00:33:30,285 --> 00:33:32,585
An abuse of power controversy? How embarrassing.

459
00:33:34,055 --> 00:33:36,695
Is that video real?

460
00:33:37,655 --> 00:33:39,025
Did you really go on bullying like that?

461
00:33:39,895 --> 00:33:41,025
I...

462
00:33:43,735 --> 00:33:45,905
I don't even know anymore.

463
00:33:46,765 --> 00:33:51,435
Well, regardless of the video, I know who you are.

464
00:33:52,105 --> 00:33:56,775
And when I was struggling before my debut, you saw one of my scripts,

465
00:33:56,875 --> 00:33:59,015
picked me, and helped me debut, so I could be successful like this.

466
00:33:59,545 --> 00:34:02,655
Of course, after that, with all your demands,

467
00:34:02,715 --> 00:34:04,785
you made my life a living hell.

468
00:34:07,225 --> 00:34:10,995
But if there's one thing about me, I remember the favours I'm owed,

469
00:34:11,125 --> 00:34:14,425
and I hold grudges. I always pay people back.

470
00:34:16,495 --> 00:34:17,535
My new project.

471
00:34:20,405 --> 00:34:22,304
It's scheduled to air in the first half of next year,

472
00:34:22,305 --> 00:34:23,375
and we're casting now.

473
00:34:24,405 --> 00:34:27,045
Thank you, Writer Oh. I'll never forget this.

474
00:34:30,045 --> 00:34:31,375
(Kang Hee)

475
00:34:31,445 --> 00:34:33,945
Oh my, the character Kang Hee is amazing.

476
00:34:34,145 --> 00:34:36,055
She has that "girl crush" vibe that's so popular now.

477
00:34:37,855 --> 00:34:38,985
Not Kang Hee.

478
00:34:40,785 --> 00:34:44,295
- What? - You've got the wrong idea.

479
00:34:44,955 --> 00:34:47,295
Not Kang Hee. This one, Hee Joo.

480
00:34:51,095 --> 00:34:54,205
Not the main character, Kang Hee,

481
00:34:55,305 --> 00:34:56,905
but the supporting role, Hee Joo?

482
00:34:57,405 --> 00:34:59,245
You're still looking for a leading role in this situation?

483
00:34:59,775 --> 00:35:01,905
You still haven't grasped your situation, have you?

484
00:35:06,245 --> 00:35:07,485
If you don't want it, then forget it.

485
00:35:09,155 --> 00:35:10,155
I'll do it.

486
00:35:12,485 --> 00:35:13,485
Hee Joo.

487
00:35:15,325 --> 00:35:17,495
But it's not confirmed yet.

488
00:35:18,995 --> 00:35:20,525
The director's a bit picky.

489
00:35:20,865 --> 00:35:23,235
With the controversy and all, he's not too keen on you.

490
00:35:23,635 --> 00:35:25,335
He'll make the final decision after seeing...

491
00:35:25,395 --> 00:35:27,035
your character analysis and your acting.

492
00:35:27,765 --> 00:35:29,435
So don't get your hopes up.

493
00:35:31,075 --> 00:35:32,975
I know exactly how skilled you are.

494
00:35:45,255 --> 00:35:46,325
Who are you?

495
00:35:48,355 --> 00:35:49,395
What is this?

496
00:35:50,195 --> 00:35:51,795
Don't tell me you ran away from home at your age...

497
00:35:53,465 --> 00:35:56,865
- You live alone. - From today until the audition,

498
00:35:57,535 --> 00:35:58,895
we're having a training camp.

499
00:35:59,905 --> 00:36:04,405
Who is? Me? Why? And says who?

500
00:36:04,475 --> 00:36:07,275
What good is a teacher who won't help? Just help me this once.

501
00:36:07,345 --> 00:36:09,415
I'm really desperate this time.

502
00:36:13,985 --> 00:36:14,985
Right.

503
00:36:15,385 --> 00:36:17,885
I was just trying to survive, doing this and that,

504
00:36:17,955 --> 00:36:19,385
and this is where I ended up.

505
00:36:19,455 --> 00:36:22,525
How about reading it with a bit more emotion, a little more naturally?

506
00:36:23,395 --> 00:36:25,525
- Right. This is where I ended up. - One more time.

507
00:36:43,645 --> 00:36:45,015
(Not "What Would I Do?" But "What Would Hee Joo Do?")

508
00:36:55,855 --> 00:36:57,595
(Visitation Room)

509
00:36:57,695 --> 00:36:59,495
(CCTV Recording In Progress)

510
00:36:59,565 --> 00:37:01,525
(Ministry Of Justice)

511
00:37:05,235 --> 00:37:06,505
Visitor for Lee Young Ji?

512
00:37:26,255 --> 00:37:29,055
I heard from the detective.

513
00:37:29,555 --> 00:37:32,295
That you hired a lawyer for me with your own money, Mr. Cha.

514
00:37:32,925 --> 00:37:34,565
And that you went to that bastard...

515
00:37:35,565 --> 00:37:36,935
and got him to agree to a settlement.

516
00:37:38,265 --> 00:37:40,465
Why would you go that far?

517
00:37:42,205 --> 00:37:43,575
For someone like me.

518
00:37:45,205 --> 00:37:46,275
I'm sorry.

519
00:37:49,975 --> 00:37:52,545
I'm sorry. It was because of my greed.

520
00:37:54,945 --> 00:37:56,315
I'm so sorry.

521
00:38:00,185 --> 00:38:01,255
I'm sorry.

522
00:38:05,655 --> 00:38:06,825
I'm sorry.

523
00:38:22,715 --> 00:38:24,815
Hey, I heard from you, but I couldn't...

524
00:38:24,875 --> 00:38:27,015
believe it. The great Yu Ji An is actually here...

525
00:38:27,085 --> 00:38:28,744
for a meeting about a supporting role.

526
00:38:28,745 --> 00:38:30,585
She must be really desperate, right?

527
00:38:30,785 --> 00:38:32,654
What's your problem? She can hear what you are saying here.

528
00:38:32,655 --> 00:38:33,655
Fine.

529
00:38:38,295 --> 00:38:40,695
- Hello. - Yes, hello.

530
00:38:48,365 --> 00:38:49,675
So, you've read the script?

531
00:38:50,605 --> 00:38:51,605
Yes.

532
00:38:52,035 --> 00:38:54,945
Let's see if you've actually analysed the character correctly.

533
00:38:56,945 --> 00:38:58,815
Episode 1, scene 35.

534
00:38:59,385 --> 00:39:00,515
Go ahead.

535
00:39:01,785 --> 00:39:02,785
Okay.

536
00:39:02,855 --> 00:39:04,785
(Season Of God, Episode 1)

537
00:39:08,025 --> 00:39:09,754
On today's Culture Walk,

538
00:39:09,755 --> 00:39:11,154
we're meeting with the couple artists...

539
00:39:11,155 --> 00:39:12,595
who recently held a solo exhibition in the US,

540
00:39:12,695 --> 00:39:16,634
- Song Jin Ho and Kim Yoo Jung. - Hello.

541
00:39:16,635 --> 00:39:19,065
You guys are such a handsome couple.

542
00:39:19,505 --> 00:39:21,705
You were voted 1 of the top 10 couples...

543
00:39:21,765 --> 00:39:23,875
envied by those in their 20s and 30s. You knew that, right?

544
00:39:24,105 --> 00:39:25,235
What's the secret?

545
00:39:26,275 --> 00:39:29,175
I think it's because we were each other's support system...

546
00:39:29,245 --> 00:39:30,645
during a very difficult time.

547
00:39:31,475 --> 00:39:35,345
When I met her, I was going through a tough time.

548
00:39:36,085 --> 00:39:40,025
During that time, she was on my side and told me that I wasn't wrong.

549
00:39:40,385 --> 00:39:41,385
And most importantly,

550
00:39:42,225 --> 00:39:44,425
she was always smiling.

551
00:39:44,855 --> 00:39:47,125
Gosh, that's so romantic.

552
00:39:49,335 --> 00:39:50,434
According to this file,

553
00:39:50,435 --> 00:39:53,835
your counselling sessions have always been quite aggressive.

554
00:39:53,935 --> 00:39:57,335
Didn't you expect that a problem like this would eventually occur?

555
00:39:57,635 --> 00:40:01,475
So you were doing so well you got arrogant? Is that it?

556
00:40:02,205 --> 00:40:03,345
That's not what I meant.

557
00:40:03,945 --> 00:40:05,175
As you all know,

558
00:40:05,845 --> 00:40:07,915
negative emotions like anger and resentment...

559
00:40:08,545 --> 00:40:11,015
are psychological motivators of human behaviour.

560
00:40:11,455 --> 00:40:13,625
I believe that rather than simply suppressing these emotions,

561
00:40:13,925 --> 00:40:16,655
rechannelling them into a useful, motivational energy source...

562
00:40:17,625 --> 00:40:20,895
- is more effective for my clients. - And what good did that do?

563
00:40:21,195 --> 00:40:24,965
- This still happened in the end. - The nerve.

564
00:40:25,395 --> 00:40:27,965
Do you have any idea how much our reputation...

565
00:40:28,035 --> 00:40:29,775
has plummeted because of you?

566
00:40:38,715 --> 00:40:40,985
What did the Association say? Did you get the results of the hearing?

567
00:40:48,525 --> 00:40:49,855
Why are you so...

568
00:40:50,455 --> 00:40:52,424
- Where are you now? - Auntie.

569
00:40:52,425 --> 00:40:53,995
She's having another episode.

570
00:41:02,365 --> 00:41:03,735
Have you ever sacrificed anything...

571
00:41:03,805 --> 00:41:05,975
for anyone in your life, Yu Ji An?

572
00:41:07,275 --> 00:41:11,115
But this character, Hee Joo, is your polar opposite.

573
00:41:11,575 --> 00:41:15,345
She's so afraid her sadness will hurt the ones she loves...

574
00:41:15,685 --> 00:41:18,115
that she can't even bring herself to cry or grieve,

575
00:41:18,185 --> 00:41:21,125
and forces herself into this painful smile.

576
00:41:22,725 --> 00:41:25,224
Having spent her whole life sacrificing for others,

577
00:41:25,225 --> 00:41:27,465
she even sacrifices her own feelings after all.

578
00:41:29,535 --> 00:41:30,695
Yu Ji An,

579
00:41:31,095 --> 00:41:34,435
do you have any idea what a pained, heartbreaking smile even is?

580
00:41:35,935 --> 00:41:37,005
Ji An, I'm sorry.

581
00:41:37,505 --> 00:41:38,775
Let's work together next time.

582
00:41:51,615 --> 00:41:52,625
What's this?

583
00:41:53,125 --> 00:41:54,285
This belongs to the person across the hall.

584
00:42:00,225 --> 00:42:01,225
Excuse me.

585
00:42:03,795 --> 00:42:05,235
I wonder why he is running in such a hurry.

586
00:42:12,175 --> 00:42:15,945
- Gosh, what took you so long? - Dad.

587
00:42:17,145 --> 00:42:19,415
It's okay, Ha Yul. Daddy's here. It's okay.

588
00:42:21,315 --> 00:42:22,815
She'd been quiet for a while,

589
00:42:22,885 --> 00:42:24,685
but her drinking problem flared up again.

590
00:42:26,055 --> 00:42:27,255
Auntie, can you watch Ha Yul for a bit?

591
00:42:27,685 --> 00:42:31,395
I'll just take her over to my place. Ha Yul, let's go to Grandma's house.

592
00:42:41,665 --> 00:42:42,805
Why only me...

593
00:42:43,335 --> 00:42:45,535
Why do I have to be the only one who's miserable? Why?

594
00:42:52,045 --> 00:42:53,715
We have to stop this. Okay?

595
00:42:54,915 --> 00:42:56,215
You'll collapse again if you keep this up.

596
00:42:58,785 --> 00:43:00,555
This is all your fault.

597
00:43:01,455 --> 00:43:03,825
I'm like this because of you.

598
00:43:12,335 --> 00:43:13,505
Please, stop.

599
00:43:17,075 --> 00:43:18,235
Just stop it.

600
00:43:19,775 --> 00:43:22,505
Fine, I'm sorry. It was my fault.

601
00:43:23,615 --> 00:43:26,585
- So, for today... - If it hadn't been for you...

602
00:43:28,315 --> 00:43:29,315
Why...

603
00:43:30,385 --> 00:43:31,455
I just wish...

604
00:43:33,285 --> 00:43:35,925
I wish it had been you instead.

605
00:43:41,695 --> 00:43:44,835
I know. I wish I had been the one who got hurt.

606
00:43:46,765 --> 00:43:48,005
It would've been better.

607
00:44:01,085 --> 00:44:02,115
Please.

608
00:44:02,885 --> 00:44:03,885
Song Hwan.

609
00:44:04,915 --> 00:44:05,915
I...

610
00:44:06,755 --> 00:44:08,185
I'm having a really hard time too.

611
00:44:11,125 --> 00:44:14,865
She's so afraid her sadness will hurt the ones she loves...

612
00:44:15,525 --> 00:44:17,935
that she can't even bring herself to cry or grieve,

613
00:44:18,065 --> 00:44:20,865
and forces herself into this painful smile.

614
00:44:22,165 --> 00:44:23,335
Yu Ji An,

615
00:44:23,775 --> 00:44:27,145
do you have any idea what a pained, heartbreaking smile even is?

616
00:44:29,175 --> 00:44:32,715
I don't think I'm the one who's crying. I think it's you.

617
00:44:33,115 --> 00:44:34,885
It really feels like I can.

618
00:44:35,285 --> 00:44:37,055
It's almost like I can really hear it.

619
00:44:37,115 --> 00:44:41,425
It's like his feelings are being conveyed to me.

